See if you're washing your hands right.
We all know that they need to be washed (e.g. when you come home or before a meal).
But not everyone knows that to actually get rid of germs, you have to do it the right way.
This is especially important now that autumn infections are approaching.
It takes at least 30-40 seconds for the washing to sufficiently remove dangerous bacteria and viruses from our hands.
Yet most of us wash them less!
All it takes is warm water and simple soap – it is not true that it must be antibacterial (many doctors even advise them against it).
By washing, we rub not only the bottoms and the tops of the hand, but also: finger tips (attached or individually) – rub them with circular motions on the inside of the second hand, spaces between fingers (stitch your hands, rubbing your fingers against each other), thumbs – each thumb is covered with a second hand and in such a embrace we turn it a moment to the right and left.
In an emergency situation (when you cannot wash your hands) we should wipe your hands with a wet handkerchief and then use antibacterial gel (in drugstores, from 5 PLN).
After using the public toilet, do not touch the hand-washed handles or doors (recommendation of the Main Sanitary Inspectorate).
Open it through a paper towel.
The President of Iran says he's turned down a proposal to talk to the US, Donald Trump denies it.
Tehran did not engage with the American side during the UN General Assembly in New York, despite the Americans' offer to abolish sanctions, said Iran's President Hasan Rowhani on Friday.
U.S. President Donald Trump commented that it was the Iranian side that requested that the restrictions be lifted, which he refused to do.
According to Iranian President Hasan Rowhani, the Americans have proposed to abolish all sanctions imposed on Tehran in exchange for negotiating a new international agreement.
It would regulate both the Iranian nuclear programme and the ballistic missile programme.
Rowhani: Iran will not engage in talks in the atmosphere of maximum pressure
The President of Iran stated that he did not agree to these talks because of the "toxic atmosphere".
He said that he had met with American diplomats because he had submitted to French, German, and Great Britain.
However, he stressed that Iran would not engage in talks in an atmosphere of "maximum pressure".
"And even if we want to negotiate with Americans in 5+1 format, no one can predict what the outcome will be," said Rowhani.
A day earlier, the Iranian leader said that he did not exclude talks with the US, and that the European parties to the nuclear agreement accused American sanctions against Iran.
He added that the sanctions imposed on Iran following the withdrawal of the U.S. nuclear agreement "are a precondition that does not allow" dialogue.
If we can lift this precondition and if America can lift sanctions and maximum pressure, then of course we can talk to America – he declared.
He added that he did not rule out a meeting with the President of the United States Donald Trump, even though he did not agree to such a conversation during the past week at the UN General Assembly.
Trump: “Iran asked, I said no”
Donald Trump tweeted that he rejected the request of the Iranian side.
“Iran wanted me to lift the sanctions imposed on them so that we could meet.
Of course, I said "no!", tweeted the President of the United States.
Tension with an atomic background agreement
France, Germany and the United Kingdom are trying to ease the tension between Washington and Tehran in order to save some form the 2015 agreement with Iran, which they were signatories to.
It provided that in return for the abolition of economic sanctions Iran would resign from the nuclear programme and that the nuclear sector would be subject to control by the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA).
Since the withdrawal of the US from the agreement in May 2015, the remaining signatories have repeatedly confirmed that they want to keep the agreement in force.
It hasn't worked out so far.
Washington uses the tactics of exerting maximum pressure on Iran, and sanctions also include a full embargo on Iranian oil.
Tehran announced that if it did not receive a licence to export raw material, it would limit its obligations under the agreement every 60 days.
