The Senate has decided on key laws
The Senate adopted without amendment the Act on the disclosure of the property of the families of the most important government officials and on flights of the most important persons in the country.
52 senators voted in favour of the amendment of the Act on the property of families of civil servants without amendments, 14 were against and three abstained.
The senators therefore decided to reject the 12 amendments tabled during the Wednesday debate by Senator Sławomir Rybicki.
According to him, the amendments were intended to "civilise" and to limit the scope of the information provided in the statement on the property situation of the own children, the children of the spouse, the children adopted to cases where the children remain in the common household with the person obliged to make the declaration.
The Act on the disclosure of the assets of the families of the most important government officials, whose project was created at the Prime Minister's office, was passed by the Sejm on 11 September.
The provisions assume that, among others, the Prime Minister, ministers, Members, MEPs, senators, Presidents: the Constitutional Court, the Supreme Administrative Court and the Supreme Court, as well as the heads of other state institutions, will be obliged to include in the statement of property information on the personal assets of spouses, children and persons who remain in a common life.
The Senate did not propose amendments to the Act on flights of the most important persons in the country.
It regulates what flights have HEAD status and who can be on board government aircraft with the most important people in the country.
The Act also specifies who is responsible for maintaining the Central Flight Register.
55 senators voted in favour of the bill, 12 were against and four abstained.
According to the bill, every flight of the president will be a flight "executed on official mission".
The president's flights will be accompanied by family members and others invited by the president.
On the other hand, the flight in the mission of the official Prime Minister and Marshals of the Sejm and the Senate will be only a flight "taken in order to carry out tasks directly related to the function".
The Act also specifies the list of persons who may accompany the most important persons in the country during the flight.
According to the regulations, members of the delegation may be on board – invited Members, senators, representatives of public authorities and experts; technical, medical or organisational staff; as well as journalists.
In accordance with the Act, in the event of doubts concerning the flights of the Marshals of the Sejm and the Senate, the Head of the National Council will ask for their clarification.
